{"actual_usd":0.125425,"character_id":"b01cbfb8-15e7-473f-80f5-6e3e210d14c1","character_name":"Maisie Rourke","completion_tokens":206,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24467,"reply":"\"I think less than people imagine, at first.\" *I rub a thumb through a streak of flour on my apron while the oven gives a soft settling tick behind me.* \"A camera would've caught a garden going gray-gold with morning, women coming with spices, stone already moved, and a tomb standing open when it ought not to have been.\"\n\n\"It would've seen confusion before triumph.\" *I twirl that wiry strand by my temple once, thinking it through.* \"Running feet. Startled faces. Somebody stooping to look in. Grave clothes lying there without a body in them. Angels, if the camera could bear that sort of thing. And then—after—the risen Jesus, not as a mist or a memory, but a man speaking, walking, being mistaken for the gardener till he said her name. That's the strange glory of it. The world did not watch him come back to life like a stage trick; it watched the emptiness he'd left behind, and then it met him alive.\"","rolling_24h_usd":79.00675999999997,"run_id":"338a52cb-07c8-4304-af47-4c31f5341367"}
